{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/pulls/983", "id": 456073192, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDU2MDczMTky", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/983", "diff_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/983.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/pyhf/pull/983.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/issues/983", "number": 983, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "feat: Add precision setting string API to set_backend", "user": {"login": "matthewfeickert", "id": 5142394, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUxNDIzOTQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5142394?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert", "html_url": "https://github.com/matthewfeickert", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "# Description\r\n\r\nResolves #982\r\n\r\nAdd the ability to set the backend precision through a `str` argument in `pyhf.set_backend`. This allows the following\r\n\r\n```python\r\n>>> import pyhf\r\n>>> pyhf.set_backend(\"pytorch\", precision=\"64b\")  # string API\r\n>>> pyhf.tensorlib.precision\r\n'64b'\r\n>>> pyhf.set_backend(pyhf.tensor.pytorch_backend(precision=\"32b\"))  # object API \r\n>>> pyhf.tensorlib.precision\r\n'32b'\r\n>>> pyhf.set_backend(\"pytorch\")  # no default, so defer to backend for precision\r\n>>> pyhf.tensorlib.precision\r\n'32b'\r\n>>> pyhf.set_backend(pyhf.tensor.pytorch_backend(precision=\"32b\"), precision=\"64b\")  # set_backend string API wins if conflict\r\n>>> pyhf.tensorlib.precision\r\n'64b'\r\n```\r\n\r\n~~Additionally, set the default backend precision for _all_ backends to `64b`.~~\r\n\r\nReadTheDocs build: https://pyhf.readthedocs.io/en/api-add-precision-to-set_backend/\r\n\r\n# Checklist Before Requesting Reviewer\r\n\r\n- [x] Tests are passing\r\n- [x] \"WIP\" removed from the title of the pull request\r\n- [x] Selected an Assignee for the PR to be responsible for the log summary\r\n\r\n# Before Merging\r\n\r\nFor the PR Assignees:\r\n\r\n- [x] Summarize commit messages into a comprehensive review of the PR\r\n\r\n```\r\n* Add support for setting backend precision through str kwarg in set_backend\r\n   - N.B.: If the kwarg is provided it will always be used even if backend is set with tensor backend object\r\n* Adopt use of the str API internally for the CLI\r\n```\r\n", "created_at": "2020-07-24T04:48:54Z", "updated_at": "2020-07-25T13:08:27Z", "closed_at": "2020-07-25T13:08:26Z", "merged_at": "2020-07-25T13:08:26Z", "merge_commit_sha": "eadcd11013eb65f8bd58f0efd87843815cabde5a", "assignees": [{"login": "matthewfeickert", "id": 5142394, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUxNDIzOTQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5142394?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert", "html_url": "https://github.com/matthewfeickert", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthewfeickert/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [{"id": 815282411, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw4MTUyODI0MTE=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/labels/feat/enhancement", "name": "feat/enhancement", "color": "a2eeef", "default": false, "description": "New feature or request"}, {"id": 1534869049, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxNTM0ODY5MDQ5", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/labels/API", "name": "API", "color": "045d6d", "default": false, "description": "Changes the public API"}], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/pulls/983/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/pulls/983/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/issues/983/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/pyhf/statuses/8b8bc83fecb826094bb14f0ac9fb4884e4a7d029", "head": {"label": "scikit-hep:api/add-precision-to-set_backend", "ref": "api/add-precision-to-set_backend", "sha": "8b8bc83fecb826094bb14f0ac9fb4884e4a7d029", "user": {"login": "scikit-hep", "id": 23454624, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjIzNDU0NjI0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23454624?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/following{/o